  "prompt": "Why can't I see views on my Instagram videos?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you can't see views on your Instagram videos:\n\n1. Technical glitch\n- Temporary app or server issue\n- Instagram might be experiencing problems\n\n2. Account settings\n- Your account might be set to private\n- You may have restricted visibility settings\n\n3. App version\n- Outdated Instagram app\n- Need to update to the latest version\n\n4. Device compatibility\n- Older device or operating system\n- Compatibility issues with the app\n\n5. Video processing\n- Video might still be processing\n- Views take time to update\n\nTroubleshooting steps:\n- Update Instagram app\n- Restart your device\n- Check your internet connection\n- Clear app cache\n- Reinstall the app\n- Ensure your account settings allow public views\n\nIf the issue persists, contact Instagram support through the app or their help center.",
